pageContext.claim: “I just know that our country is looking into the corruption of the 2016 election. It was a corrupt election, whether it's Comey; or McCabe; or Strzok or his lover, Lisa Page -- the two great lovers. There was a lot of corruption. Maybe it goes right up to President Obama. I happen to think it does. But you look at Brennan, and you look at Clapper, and you get some real beauties.”
pageContext.analysis: A comprehensive DOJ Inspector General report issued in December 2019 found no evidence for many of Trump's conspiracy theories about the FBI investigation, including claims that the FBI spied on his campaign, that the FBI planted informants on the campaign, that FBI tried to entrap campaign aides or that they tried to overthrow his presidency.
